Scripts
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
parser.py > Parser for language to be compiled. It uses PLY and hence yacc implementation.
lexer.py > Lexer for language to be compiled. It uses PLY and hence lex implementation.
parser > Shell script to parse given test file and generate html output via html.cpp.
html.cpp > Code for generating html output. Invoked by parser shell script.

Steps to execute
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ cd asgn3/
$ make
$ bin/parser test/test1.cs


Output files
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
right_derivation.html :  This .html file contains the LR parsing tree of the input program
The non-terminal being expanded are marked in a different color/bold-faced/underlined etc.


Implementation Details
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Here we have tried to implement most of the features listed below:

Variable declarations:Int,Float,Char,String
New operator
Object_declaration
ForStatement
If-Else Statement
Array declaration
Boolean implementation
Access modifiers
Operators : +,-,*,/ ..etc
Assign and Compare operators

